President Muhammadu Buhari, who was in Daura, Katsina state for the Presidential and National Assembly elections, is on his way back to Abuja. Buhari, who left the helipad in GRA area of Daura, close to his residence via chopper around 10:am, landed at the Umaru Yar’adua airport in Katsina at 10:25am. Our correspondent reports that the president left the katsina airport at 10:47am to Abuja, via presidential aircraft. Recall that the president arrived Katsina State last Friday for the Presidential and National Assembly elections. Buhari arrives Daura for elections Buhari, Aisha in Daura for today’s elections Buhari returns to Abuja after election shift